page.text: Fort Stewart Accident Summary Report - 144 Corridor
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT AT THE ABOVE TIME, DATE AND LOCATION, XXXXXX OPERATING A WHITE IN COLOR, 2006, CHEVROLET, EXPRESS, WHICH BELONGED TO AIR SERVICES AND
REFRIGERATION INC, STRUCK A DEER THAT HAD ENTERED THE ROADWAY. THE COMAPNY VEHICLE SUSTAINED A BROKEN DRIVERS SIDE HEADLIGHT ASSEMBLY. THERE WERE NO INJURIES REPORTED
AND SEATBELTS WERE UTILIZED. THERE WAS NO APPARENT DRUG OR ALCOHOL INVOLVEMENT. THIS IS A FINAL REPORT.
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT AT THE ABOVE TIME, DATE AND LOCATION, XXXXX OPERATING A GREY IN COLOR, 2005 CHEVROLET IMPALA, FAILED TO MAINTAIN HER LANE OF TRAVEL AND RAN OFF
THE HIGHWAY. XXXXXX VEHICLE SUSTAINED WATER DAMAGE TO THE ENTIRE UNDERCARRIAGE OF THE VEHICLE, THE INTERIOR, THE TRUCK AND THE THE ENGINE. NO INJURIES WERE REPORTED.
THERE WAS NO APPARENT DRUG OR ALCOHOL INVOLVEMENT. THIS IS A FINAL REPORT.
SEE ATTACHED (4 car accident, v3 and v4 both sedans)
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT AT THE ABOVE TIME, DATE AND LOCATION, SCHECHTER OPERATING A WHITE IN COLOR, 2003 THOMAS 44 PASSENGER BUS, L/P# (GOVT) G32-01431, FAILED TO
MAINTAIN LANE BY FALLING ASLEEP BEHIND THE WHEEL AND STRUCK A YELLOW AND BLACK IN COLOR STRIPED, TRAFFIC DEFLECTOR SIGN AFFIXED TO A WOODEN POLE. DAMAGE TO THE GOVERNMENT
BUS CONSISTED OF A BROKEN RIGHT SIDE WINDSHIELD. TRAFFIC DEFLECTOR SIGN WAS DESTROYED. THERE WERE NO INJURIES REPORTED AND SEATBELTS WERE UTILIZED. THERE WAS NO APPARENT
DRUG OR ALCOHOL USE INVOLVEMENT. THIS IS A FINAL REPORT.
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT AT THE ABOVE TIME, DATE AND LOCATION, WEAVER DRIVING A WHITE IN COLOR, 1996 BUICK REGAL, L/P #(GA/07) ZZONE, FAILED TO YEILD THE RIGHT OF WAY
CAUSING LOUD TO STRIKE HER VEHICLE. LOUD OPERATING A GREEN IN COLOR, 1998 FORD EXPEDITION, L/P #(GA/07) ABM4229, IMPROPERLY PASSED WEAVER WHILE SHE WAS IN THE PROCESS OF A U-
TURN AND STRUCK HER VEHICLE. WEAVER'S VEH SUSTAINED DENTS AND SCRATCHES TO THE LEFT FRONT BUMPER, LEFT FRONT FENDER AND THE LEFT FRONT DOOR, AND BROKE THE LEFT SIDE VIEW
MIRROR.LOUD'S VEHICLE SUSTAINED DENTS AND SCRATCHES TO THE RIGHT FRONT BUMPER, RIGHT FRONT FENDER, RIGHT FRONT DOOR, AND THE RIGHT REAR DOOR. A CHECK OF THE GCIC REVEALED
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT AT THE ABOVE TIME, DATE AND LOCATION, CLARK OPERATING A RED IN COLOR, 2000 JAGUAR S-TYPE, L/P #(GA/08) AEB3012 STRUCK A DEER THAT HAD ENTERED THE
ROADWAY. CLARK’S VEHICLE SUSTAINED DISABLING DAMAGE THAT CONSISTED OF CRACKED GRILL, DENTS AND SCRATCHES TO THE LEFT FRONT BUMPER, LEFT FRONT FENDER, HOOD AND A BROKEN
LEFT HEADLIGHT. THERE WERE NO INJURIES REPORTED AND SEATBELTS WERE UTILIZED. THERE WAS NO APPARENT DRUG OR ALCOHOL INVOLVEMENT. THIS IS A FINAL REPORT.
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT AT THE ABOVE TIME, DATE AND LOCATION, WATERS OPERATING A YELLOW IN COLOR 2006 CHEVROLET COLORADO L/P# (MA/07) 26T112 FAILED TO EXERCISE DUE CARE
BY FALLING ASLEEP BEHIND THE WHEEL OF HIS VEHICLE. WATER'S OVER CORRECTED WHEN HE REENTERED THE ROAD AND ROLLED THE VEHICLE OVER. DAMAGE CONSISTED OF DISABLING DENTING TO
THE FRONT, TOP AND SIDES OF THE VEHICLE. WATERS WAS TRANSPORTED BY EMS TO SAVANNAH MEMORIAL. HE WAS RELEASED WITH X5 STITCHES TO HIS LEFT EYE AND SCRAPES TO HIS KNEE AND
ELBOW. S&K TOWING TOWED THE VEHICLE TO THIER STORAGE LOT. INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT WATER'S HAD UTILIZED HIS SEATBELTS AND NO SIGN OF DRUG OR ALCOHOL INVOLVEMENT. FINAL
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT AT THE ABOVE TIME, DATE AND LOCATION, GLISSON OPERATING A 2004 TOYOTA TACOMA L/P# (GA/07) ABM4842 FAILED TO EXERCISE DUE CARE BY FALLING ASLEEP
BEHIND THE WHEEL OF HIS MOVING VEHICLE. GLISSON OVER CORRECTED WHEN HE REENTERED THE ROAD AND ROLLED THE VEHICLE OVER. DAMAGE CONSISTED OF DISABLING DENTING TO THE
FRONT, TOP AND SIDES OF THE VEHICLE. GLISSON WAS TRANSPORTED BY EMS TO LIBERTY MEMORIAL. HE WAS RELEASED WITHOUT REPORT OF INJURY AND GIVEN MOTRIN FOR PAIN. BLOUNT TOWING
TOWED THE VEHICLE TO THE OWNERS HOUSE. FURTHER INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT GLISSON HAD UTILIZED HIS SEATBELTS AND HAD NO SIGN OF DRUG OR ALCOHOL INVOLVEMENT. THIS IS A
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT XXXX OPERATING A SILVER 2003 DODGE RAM 1500 STRUCK A DEER THAT ENTERED ONTO THE SURFACE OF THE ROADWAY. DAMAGE TO XXXXX VEHICLE CONSISTED OF
A MISALIGNED HOOD, DENTED GRILL, AND A DENTED BUMPER WHICH CAUSED DISABLING DAMAGE NOT ALLOWING THE LEFT FRONT TIRE TO TURN. THERE WERE NO INJURIES REPORTED AND
SEATBELTS WERE UTILIZED. THERE WAS NO APPARENT DRUG OR ALCOHOL INVOLVEMENT. XXXXX VEHICLE WAS TOWED BY ATS WRECKER SERVICE TO THEIR STORAGE LOT.
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT AT 0850HRS, 22 JUN 07, XXXX OPERATING A GREY IN COLOR, 2005 TOYOTA SCION TC, WAS TRAVELLING WEST ON GA HWY 144 AT M/M #0 BRYAN CO WHEN HE FAILED
TO MAINTAIN CONTROL OF HIS VEHICLE AFTER HE HAD LOST CONSCIOUSNESS DUE TO ILLNESS CAUSING HIS VEHICLE EXIT THE HIGHWAY AND STRIKE A TELEPHONE POLE.
AT 1140 HRS, ON 20 JULY 07, XXXX OPERATING A BLACK IN COLOR, 1994 FORD EXPLORER L/P# , STRUCK 2 COWS WHILE HE WAS TRAVELING WEST ON GA HWY #144W.
SYNOPSIS: AT 1350 HRS, XXXX DRIVING A 2004, SILVER IN COLOR, GMC ENVOY, TRAVELING ON 144E, MM17 LOST CONTROL OF HER VEHICLE WHILE TRAVELING TOO FAST FOR CONDITIONS. XXXXXX
VEHICLE EXITED THE ROADWAY STRUCK A MILE MARKER SIGN AND A TREE. DAMAGE TO XXXXXX VEHICLE WAS DISABLING DAMAGE. THE ACCIDENT WAS CAUSED BY SPEED TOO FAST FOR CONDITIONS.
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT AT 0530 HRS, 18 SEP 07, A WHITE IN COLOR , 2005 SUZUKI FORENZA L/P# WAS TRAVELING WEST ON HWY 144 E AT APPROX MM # 12 WHEN A DEER RAN OUT INTO
THE ROAD IN FRONT OF XXXXXX AND GOT STRUCK. DAMAGES TO THE WHITE IN COLOR , 2005 SUZUKI FORENZA L/P# (GA/08) AVK2970 WAS A DENTED HOOD, BUMPER, LEFT AND RIGHT FRONT
FENDERS, GRILL, RADIATOR, AND RIGHT SIDE HEADLIGHT. THIS IS A FINAL REPORT
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT AT 0530 HRS, 2 OCT 07, A WHITE IN COLOR, 2006 CHEVROLET COLORADO, OWNED BY THE GOVERNMENT, OPERATED BY XXXXX WAS TRAVELING WEST ON HWY 144E MM
#4 WHEN A DEER RAN OUT IN THE ROAD AND XXXX DID NOT HAVE TIME TO STOP CAUSING HIM TO STRIKE THE DEER. DAMAGES TO THE WHITE IN COLOR, 2006 CHEVROLET COLORADO, BY THE
GOVERNMENT, OPERATED BY XXXXXX WERE A BROKEN RIGHT FRONT HEADLIGHT ASSEMBLY, DENTED RIGHT DOOR AND FRONT RIGHT FENDER. THIS IS A FINAL REPORT.
TRAVELIN ON 144 EAST DEER RAN ACROOS THE HIGHWAY INDIVIDUAL WAS NOT ABLE TO ELUDE IT WITHOUT CAUSING MORE DAMAGE TO THE VEHICLE OR TO HERSELF.
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT AT APPROX 0634 HRS, ON 23 OCT 07, FT STEWART POLICE (CURRY) WAS DISPATCHED TO GA HWY# 144E, M/M# 18 FOR A T/A (VEHICLE TO DEER). UPON ARRIVAL,
CONTACT WAS MADE WITH XXXXXX, OPERATING A 2002 CHEVROLET SILVERADO, L/P # STRUCK A DEER THAT HAD ENTERED THE ROADWAY. DAMAGE TO XXXXXXX VEHICLE CONSISTED OF MINOR
DENTING TO THE FRONT BUMPER AND GRILL AREA. THERE WERE NO REPORT OF INJURIES AND SEATBELTS WERE STATED TO BE UTILIZED. THERE WAS NO DRUG OR ALCOHOL INVOLVEMENT. ECOD IS
UNKNOWN. THIS IS A FINAL REPORT.
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT AT THE ABOVE TIME, DATE AND LOCATION, XXXXXXXX OPERATING A SILVER IN COLOR, 2001, FORD FOCUS, OWNED BY XXXXX, FAILED TO MAINTAIN HER LANE OF
TRAFFIC AND DROVE INTO THE SHOULDER OF THE ROAD. CHESTNUT STATED SHE ATTEMPTED TO GO AROUND A CHAIR IN THE ROADWAY AND LOST CONTROL OF THE VEHICLE. DAMAGE TO THE
VEHICLE CONSISTED OF A RIGHT FRONT FLAT TIRE AND CRACK IN THE FRONT BUMPER. NO REPORT OF INJURIES. THIS IS A FINAL REPORT
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT AT THE ABOVE TIME, DATE AND LOCATION, XXXXXXX, OPERATING A BLACK IN COLOR, 2005 NISSAN SENTRA, STRUCK A DEER. DAMAGE TO XXXXXXX' VEHICLE
CONSISTED OF A BROKEN LEFT HEAD LIGHT AND A DENT TO THE FRONT LEFT QUARTER PANEL. THERE WERE NO REPORT OF INJURIES AND SEATBELTS WERE STATED TO BE UTILIZED. THERE WAS NO
APPARENT DRUG OR ALCOHOL INVOLVEMENT. THIS IS A FINAL REPORT.
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT AT 0615 HRS, 28 NOV 07, XXXX, OPERATING A WHITE IN COLOR, 2008 TOYOTA CAMRY STRUCK A DEER. DAMAGE TO XXXX VEHICLE CONSISTED OF A BROKEN RIGHT
HEADLIGHT, DENTED FRONT BUMPER, DENTED HOOD, DENTED LEFT FRONT QUARTER PANEL, DENTED DRIVERS DOOR AND A BROKEN WINDSHIELD. THERE WERE NO REPORT OF INJURIES AND
SEATBELTS WERE STATED TO BE UTILIZED. THERE WAS NO APPARENT DRUG OR ALCOHOL INVOLVEMENT. THIS IS A FINAL REPORT.
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT AT THE ABOVE TIME, DATE AND LOCATION, XXXXXX, OPERATING A WHITE IN COLOR, 2003 CHEVY TAHOE , STRUCK A DEER THAT HAD ENTERED THE ROADWAY. DAMAGE
TO XXXXXX’S VEHICLE CONSISTED OF A BROKEN RIGHT HEAD LIGHT, DENTED FRONT QUARTER PANEL, AND CRACKED GRILL GUARD. THERE WAS NO REPORT OF INJURIES AND SEAT BELTS WERE STATED
TO BE UTILIZED. THERE WAS NO APPARENT ALCOHOL OR DRUG INVOLVEMENT. THIS IS A FINAL REPORT.
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT ON THE ABOVE TIME, DATE, AND LOCATION, XXXX, WHILE OPERATING A WHITE IN COLOR, 2000 FORD F150 L/P# , FAILED TO THE STOP AT A POSTED STOP SIGN AND
EXITED THE ROADWAY. DAMAGE TO THE VEHICLE CONSISTED OF SMASHED FRONT BUMPER, MINOR SCRATCHES AND DENTS TO THE FRONT LEFT AND RIGHT QUARTER PANEL, AND (2) FRONT TIRES
BLOWN. THERE WERE NO REPORTED INJURIES. THERE WAS NO APPARENT DRUG OR ALCOHOL INVOLVEMENT. ECOD IS UNKNOWN. THIS IS A FINAL REPORT.
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT ON THE ABOVE DATE, TIME, AND LOCATION xxxxx, OPERATING A BLUE IN COLOR, 1999 FORD CONTOUR , WAS ATTEMPTING TO AVOID COLLISION WITH ANIMAL IN
ROADWAY ON HWY 144E MM #9, WHEN XXXX ROLLED HER VEHICLE ON THE SIDE OF THE ROADWAY. DAMAGE TO XXXXX' VEHICLE CONSISTED OF DENTS TO THE FRONT CENTER ROOF, FRONT CENTER
HOOD, RIGHT FRONT AND REAR DOORS, LEFT FRONT DOOR, AND WINDSHIELD. XXXXX' VEHICLE WAS TOWED BY SIMMONS WRECKER SERVICE TO THEIR STORAGE LOT. THERE WERE NO INJURIES
REPORTED AND SEATBELTS WERE STATED TO BE UTILIZED. THERE WAS NO APPARENT DRUG OR ALCOHOL INVOLVEMENT. ECOD IS UNKNOWN. THIS IS A FINAL REPORT.
INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT AT THE ABOVE TIME, DATE AND LOCATION, XXXX OPERATING A WHITE IN COLOR 2006 DODGE CARAVAN STRUCK A DEER THAT HAD ENTERED THE ROADWAY. VEHICLE
SUSTAINED DAMAGE TO THE FRONT OF THE VEHICLE HOOD, BUMPER, GRILL, AND RIGHT FRONT HEADLIGHT. THERE WERE NO INJURIES REPORTED AND SEATBELTS WERE UTILIZED. THERE WAS NO
APPARENT DRUG OR ALCOHOL INVOLVEMENT. THIS IS A FINAL REPORT.
DRIVER WHILE OPERATING A BROWN IN COLOR, 1992 PLYMOUTH VOYAGER, FAILED TO MAINTAIN HER LANE OF TRAVEL, VEERED INTO THE OPPOSITE LANE OF TRAVEL, RAN OFF THE ROADWAY AND
STRUCK A TREE. DAMAGE TO VEHICLE CONSISTED OF DISABLING IMPACT DAMAGE TO THE FRONT LEFT OF VEHICLE, THE FRONT LEFT FENDER AND THE FRONT LEFT DOOR, ALSO THE HOOD AND ROOF
WAS BENT WITH MULTIPLE CRACKS TO THE FRONT WINDSHIELD AND THERE WAS APPARENT DAMAGE TO THE UNDERCARRIAGE. DRIVER COMPLAINED OF PAIN TO HER LEGS, ARMS, NECK, BACK AND
HEAD, DRIVER TRANSPORTED TO LIBERTY REGIONAL HOSPITAL FOR FURTHER EVALUATION. DRIVER WAS RELEASED FROM THE LIBERTY REGIONAL WITH BRUISES TO HER LEFT LEG, LEFT ARM, RIGHT
DRIVER OPERATING A BLUE IN COLOR, 2001 CHEVROLET PICKUP, WHILE ATTEMPTING TO PULL FROM THE SIDE OF THE ROADWAY, SLID INTO THE DITCH. DRIVER’S VEHICLE SUSTAINED DAMAGE TO THE
FRONT BUMPER RIGHT SIDE ROCKER PANEL AND TO THE STEERING ROD. THERE WERE NO INJURIES REPORTED AND SEATBELTS WERE UTILIZED.
D1 WHILE OPERATING A BLUE IN COLOR, 2007 CHEVROLET EXPRESS VAN, MADE AN IMPROPER LEFT TURN AND STRUCK D2OPERATING A BLACK IN COLOR, 2005 HARLEY DAVIDSON FXSTI. DAMAGE TO
D2S VEHICLE CONSISTED OF BROKEN HEADLIGHT, BROKEN MIRRORS, SEVERAL DENTS AND SCRATCHES TO THE ENTIRE BODY CAUSING DISABLING DAMAGE TO THE MOTORCYCLE. DAMAGE TO D1S
VEHICLE CONSISTED OF BENDING OF THE FRONT RIGHT BUMPER AREA, HOOD, GRILL, FENDER, A BROKEN RIGHT HEADLIGHT AND TURN SIGNAL. D2 SUSTAINED MINOR LACERATIONS TO BOTH
ELBOWS, RIGHT KNEE AND RIGHT ANKLE AND WAS TRANSPORTED TO THE LIBERTY REGIONAL MEDICAL CENTER BY EMS FOR TREATMENT. NO OTHER INJURIES WERE REPORTED. SEATBELTS AND
D1 WHO WAS OPERATING A BLUE IN COLOR 2006 CHRYSLER SEBRING, STRUCK THE REAR BUMPER OF D2'S GREEN IN COLOR 2004 JEEP WRANGLER, WHICH WAS STOPPED AT A STOP SIGN AT GATE# 3.
DAMAGE CONSISTED OF A SMALL SCRATCH TO D2'S LEFT REAR BUMPER.
D1 OPERATING A BLUE IN COLOR, 1999 FORD F-150, WAS FOLLOWING TOO CLOSELY AND STRUCK THE REAR BUMPER OF A GOLD IN COLOR, 2006 NISSAN ALTIMA, OPERATED BY D2. D2 COMPLAINED OF
NECK PAIN AND WAS TRANSPORTED TO WACH ER BY FT STEWART EMS FOR TREATMENT. DAMAGE TO D1'S VEHICLE CONSISTED OF A CRACKED AND DENTED FRONT BUMPER WITH SCRATCHES. DAMAGE
TO D2'S VEHICLE CONSISTED OF A CRACKED AND DENTED REAR BUMPER AND A BENT TRUNK LID.
WHITE IN COLOR 2007 CHEVY IMPALA WAS TRAVELING EAST BOUND ON HIGWAY 144 WHEN A DEER RAN IN FRONT OF HIS VEHICLE. DRIVER STATED THAT HE DID NOT HAVE TIME TO SWERVE AND MISS
THE DEER AND STRUCK THE DEER HEAD ON
D1 OPERATING A BROWN IN COLOR 1993 HONDA ACCORD LX 4 DR, WAS FOLLOWING TO CLOSELY BEHIND D2, OPERATING A SILVER IN COLOR 2005 CHEVY MALIBU 4 DR, AS HE SLOWED DOWN AT A
YIELD SIGN, CAUSING D1 TO STRIKE D2’S VEHICLE, CAUSING DAMAGE TO THE LEFT REAR BUMPER OF D2’S VEHICLE AND LEFT FRONT BUMPER OF D1’S VEHICLE. SEATBELTS WERE STATED AS BEING
DRIVER OPERATING A SILVER IN COLOR, 2006 CHEVROLET COBALT, STRUCK A DEER WHEN IT ENTERED THE SURFACE OF THE ROADWAY.
DRIVER OPERATING A YELLOW IN COLOR, 2003 CHEVY S-10, FAILED TO MAINTAIN HIS LANE OF TRAVEL AND STRUCK THE WOOD LINE. INVESTIGATION REVEALED THAT MARTIN HAD SWERVED TO MISS
DEER THAT WERE CROSSING IN HIS LANE OF TRAVEL. SEAT BELTS WERE REPORTED AS BEING UTILIZED.
DRIVER OPERATING A SILVER IN COLOR, 2004 CHEVROLET TRAILBLAZER, STRUCK A DEER. DAMAGE TO VEHICLE CONSISTED OF DENTS AND CRACKS TO THE LEFT FRONT FENDER, BOTH RIGHT AND LEFT
HEADLIGHTS HAVE PARTS BROKEN OFF OF THEM, THE MAJORITY OF THE GRILL IS MISSING, FRONT BUMPER IS CRACKED AND OUT OF ALIGNMENT WITH THE FRONT OF THE VEHICLE, AND THE HOOD IS
DRIVER OPERATING A WHITE IN COLOR 1998 PONTIAC SUNFIRE, WAS TRAVELING NORTH BOUND TOWARD FSGA GATE #13 ADJACENT HWY 144W IN FOGGY CONDITIONS WITH LIMITED VISIBILITY
APPROACHING A STOP SIGN AT A HIGH RATE OF SPEED WHEN DRIVER SLAMMED ON THE BRAKES AND SLID INTO THE DITCH ACROSS HWY 144W. DAMAGE TO VEHICLE CONSISTED OF FRONT
UNDERCARRIAGE DAMAGE AND A CRACKED WINDSHIELD ON THE PASSENGER SIDE. AIR BAGS WERE DEPLOYED AND SEATBELTS WERE STATED TO BE UTILIZED.
D1 OPERATING A TAN IN COLOR, 2008 HONDA CIVIC, FAILED TO YIELD THE RIGHT OF WAY AT A STOP SIGN AND WAS STRUCK BY A GRAY IN COLOR, 2008 CHRYSLER PT CRUISER, OPERATED BY D2.
D1 OPERATING A WHITE IN COLOR, BLUEBIRD BUS, STRUCK THE REAR END OF A GREEN IN COLOR, CHEVELOTE C6500 FLATBED, DRIVEN BY D2, WHICH WAS ON HWY 144E MM11. THERE WAS SEVERE
DAMAGE TO THE FRONT OF D1'S VEHICLE, D1'S VEHICLE HAD TO BE TOWED BY ATS TOWING SERVICES TO TMP. DAMAGE TO D2'S VEHICLE CONSISTED OF BENDING OF THE DRAW BAR HITCH ON THE
REAR OF THE VEHICLE. D1 SUSTAIN INJURY TO HIS MIDDLE PELVIC AREA BY BEING SLIDE UP TO THE STEERING WHEEL COLUMN.
DRIVER OPERATING A WHITE IN COLOR, 2002 NISSAN ALTIMA, STRUCK A DEER WHEN IT ENTERED THE SURFACE OF THE HIGHWAY. DAMAGE TO VEHICLE CONSISTED OF DISABLING DAMAGE TO THE
LEFT FRONT QUARTERPANEL, LEFT SIDE OF THE UNDERCARRIAGE, AND LEFT SIDE OF FRONT BUMPER WAS RIPPED ALMOST COMPLETELY OFF. HINESVILLE TOWING TOWED THE VEHICLE TO THEIR
STORAGE. SEATBELTS WERE STATED AS BEING UTILIZED. THERE WERE NO INJURIES.
DRIVER OPERATING A BLACK IN COLOR 2002 FORD RANGER, WAS TRAVELING EAST ON HWY 144W, MM #0, WHEN HE VEERED ONTO THE SHOULDER OF THE HIGHWAY. DRIVER ATTEMPTED TO CORRECT
HIS PATH OF TRAVEL AND LOST CONTROL OF THE VEHICLE RESULTING IN A ROLL OVER. DAMAGE TO VEHICLE CONSISTED OF A BROKEN WINDSHIELD, BROKEN DRIVER SIDE AND PASSENGER SIDE
WINDOW, CRUSHED ROOF, DENTED PASSENGER SIDE DOOR, DENTED LEFT DRIVER SIDE FENDER, BROKEN PASSENGER SIDE TAIL LIGHT. DRIVER WAS OPERATING HIS CD PLAYER AND TOOK HIS EYES
OFF OF THE ROAD WHEN HE VEERED OFF ONTO THE SHOULDER.
DRIVER OPERATING A FORD F350 AMBULANCE, STRUCK A DEER. DAMAGE TO THE AMBULANCE CONSISTED OF A DENT TO THE RIGHT FRONT QUARTER PANEL.
DRIVER OPERATING A WHITE IN COLOR, 2004 CHEVROLET MINI VAN, WAS TRAVELING EAST ON GA HWY 144 E AT APPROXIMATELY MILE MARKER # 12 WHEN AN ANIMAL ENTERED INTO THE ROAD WAY
CAUSING DRIVER TO STRIKE THE HOG. DAMAGE TO THE VAN CONSISTED OF MINOR FUNCTIONAL DAMAGE. SEAT BELTS WERE STATED AS BEING UTILIZED.
D1 REPORTED THAT WHILE STOPPED IN HIS GREEN IN COLOR, 1994 DODGE RAM, HE WAS STRUCK FROM THE REAR BY A RED IN COLOR, 1991 BUICK PARK AVENUE, OPERATED BY D2 WHO WAS
FOLLOWING TO CLOSE. THERE WAS NO VISIBLE DAMAGE TO D1'S VEHICLE. DAMAGE TO D2'S VEHICLE CONSISTED OF A DENTED FRONT BUMPER. D1 COMPLAINED OF A SORE BACK, BUT DECLINED
MEDICAL TREATMENT. THERE WERE NO OTHER INJURIES REPORTED. SEATBELTS WERE STATED AS BEING UTILIZED.
DRIVER OPERATING A RED IN COLOR, 2007 TOYOTA CAMRY STRUCK A DEER, WHICH HAD ENTERED THE ROADWAY, CAUSING HER TO LOSE CONTROL OF HER VEHICLE AND DRIVE INTO A DITCH. DAMAGE
TO VEHICLE CONSISTED OF DENTS AND SCRATCHES TO THE FRONT RIGHT BUMPER WHICH WAS SCRATCHED, SCUFFED AND BENT UNDER THE VEHICLE, THE LEFT REAR DOOR AND LEFT REAR QUARTER
PANEL BEING DENTED, SCRATCHED AND SCUFFED. THERE WERE NO INJURIES REPORTED AND SEATBELTS WERE STATED TO BEING UTILIZED.
DRIVER OPERATING A SILVER IN COLOR 1999, LINCOLN MERCURY, STRUCK A DEER, DAMAGE TO VEHICLE CONSISTED OF CRACKS TO THE FRONT GRILL. THERE WERE NO INJURIES REPORTED AND
SEATBELTS WERE STATED TO BEING UTILIZED.
D1 OPERATING A WHITE IN COLOR, 2002 NISSAN ALTIMA, FAILED TO MAINTAIN LANE AND WAS STRUCK BY D2 OPERATING A GREEN IN COLOR 1997 DODGE RAM. D1’S VEHICLE SUSTAINED MAJOR DENTS
TO THE ENTIRE VEHICLE. D2’S VEHICLE SUSTAINED MAJOR DENTS TO THE FRONT. D1'S INJURIES INCLUDED BLUNT FORCE TRAUMA RESULTING IN DEATH AT THE HOSPITAL. D2'S INJURIES INCLUDED
COLLAR BONE, NECK, AND CHEST PAINS. SEATBELTS WERE UTILIZED.
DRIVER OPERATING A RED IN COLOR, 2005 FORD TAURUS, STRUCK A DEER. DAMAGE TO VEHICLE CONSISTED OF A DENT ON THE RIGHT FRONT FENDER. THERE WERE NO INJURIES REPORTED AND
SEATBELTS WERE STATED TO BEING UTILIZED.
D1 WAS OPERATING A RED 1998 MASSEY FERGUSON 271 TRACTOR WHEN THE LEFT FRONT TIRE BLEW, CAUSING D1 TO SWERVE INTO THE ONCOMING LANE AND STRIKE D2, OPERATING A WHITE 2003
CHEVROLET VENTURE. D1'S VEHICLE SUSTAINED DAMAGE TO THE LEFT FRONT END AND TIRE. D2'S VEHICLE SUSTAINED SCRATCHES, DENTS, SCUFFS AND A TEAR TO THE LEFT SIDE DOORS AND LEFT
REAR QUARTER PANEL. THERE WERE NO INJURIES REPORTED AND SEATBELTS WERE UTILIZED.
VECHILE WAS TRAVELING NORTH WEST ON GA 47 WHEN BJORK STRUCK A DEER ON THE FRONT RIGHT SIDE OF HIS VEHICLE. HE PROCEEDED TO SLOW DOWN AND PULL OVER ON THE SHOULDER OF THE
DRIVER WHILE OPERATING A WHITE IN COLOR, 1997 FORD F150, REPORTED THAT WHILE TRAVELING EAST BOUND ON GA HWY 47 A DEER RAN ACROSS THE ROADWAY AND STRUCK HIS VEHICLE.
DAMAGE TO VEHICLE CONSISTED OF A DENT TO FRONT LEFT DOOR, A DENT TO THE FRONT FENDER, THE FRONT LEFT HEAD LIGHT BEING SHATTERED AND A CRACKED GRILL. THERE WERE NO INJURIES
REPORTED AND SEATBELTS WERE STATED AS TO BEING UTILIZED.
DRIVER OPERATING A WHITE IN COLOR, 2001 CHEVROLET EXPRESS 3500, STRUCK AN UNKNOWN OBJECT. DAMAGE TO VEHICLE CONSISTED OF A MINOR DENT AND SCRATCHES TO THE DRIVER'S SIDE
D1 OPERATING A WHITE 1985 CHRYSLER 5TH AVENUE, FAILED TO EXERCISE DUE CARE (HIS FOOT SLIPPED OFF THE BRAKE AND HIT THE GAS PEDAL) AND STRUCK D2 OPERATING A WHITE 1999
CHEVROLET EXPRESS VAN, D1'S VEHICLE SUSTAINED CRACKED PAINT AND SCRATCHES TO THE ENTIRE FRONT FENDER. D2'S VEHICLE SUSTAINED A BENT REAR FENDER. D2'S PASSENGER, P1, DID NOT
UTILIZE HIS SEATBELT AND COMPLAINED OF LEFT KNEE, LEFT SHOULDER AND NECK PAIN. NO FURTHER INJURIES WERE REPORTED AND FORD AND OWEN UTILIZED THEIR SEATBELTS.
D1 OPERATING A TAN IN COLOR 2008 HMMWV M1165A1, FAILED TO MAINTAIN HIS LANE OF TRAVEL AND STRUCK A BLACK IN COLOR, 2007 PONTIAC G6 OPERATED BY D2. DAMAGE TO THE HMMWV
CONSISTED OF DENTS TO THE FRONT OF VEHICLE, BOTH FRONT HEADLAMPS SHATTERED, CRACKS TO THE HOOD, ALL SIDE WINDOWS OUT, SCRAPES TO THE ROOF, A BLOWN LEFT FRONT TIRE AND THE
TIE ROD SNAPPED. DAMAGE TO D2'S VEHICLE CONSISTED OF SEVERE DAMAGE TO THE ENTIRE FRONT OF THE CAR, LEFT DOOR RIPPED OFF, THE HOOD AND ROOF WERE RIPPED OFF, THE FRONT
WINDSHIELD WAS SHATTERED AND THE DRIVERS AIRBAG DEPLOYED. D1 AND HIS PASSENGERS, P1 AND P2 WERE TRANSPORTED BY EMS TO WINN ARMY HOSPITAL WERE THEY WERE TREATED AND
DRIVER OPERATING A GRAY IN COLOR, 2009 TOYOTA CAMRY, FAILED TO MAINTAIN LANE OF TRAVEL, LOST CONTROL OF HER VEHICLE AND RAN OFF THE ROADWAY. DAMAGE TO VEHICLE CONSISTED OF
A BENT HOOD, LEFT AND RIGHT FENDER, A BROKEN FRONT BUMPER, LEFT AND RIGHT HEADLIGHTS. DENTS AND SCRATCHES TO THE FRONT BUMPER, HOOD, LEFT FRONT FENDER, RIGHT FRONT FENDER
AND UNDERCARRIAGE. DRIVER SUSTAINED MINOR BONE FRACTURES TO HER RIGHT EYE AND NASAL BONE. THERE WERE NO OTHER INJURIES REPORTED AND SEATBELTS WERE STATED TO BEING
D1 OPERATING A GRAY IN COLOR, 1995 FORD F150, STRUCK A BLACK IN COLOR, 2005 TOYOTA TACOMA, OWNED BY D2, WHICH WAS STOPPED AT A STOP SIGN AT THE INTERSECTION OF GA HWY 47 AND
